
[1]hornblend

   HORN'BLEND, n. A mineral of several varieties, called by Hauy
   amphibole. It is sometimes in regular distinct crystals; more generally
   the result of confused crystallization, appearing in masses, composed
   of lamins, acicular crystals or fibers, variously aggregated. Its
   prevailing colors are black and green.
